<h4 class = "page-header">Install Apple Xcode Command Line Tools</h2>
<p><strong>Instruction</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Install the command line tools by entering the following command into your terminal.</li>
  <pre>xcode-select --install</pre>
  <li>Restart your computer.</li>
  <li>Verify that the installation was successful.</li>
  <pre>xcode-select -p</pre>
  <li>Typing the above should return the following:</li>
  <pre>/Library/Developer/CommandLineTools</pre>
</ol>
<p><strong>Reason</strong></p>
<p>Installation of many common Unix-based tools requires a GCC compiler. The Xcode Command Line Tools include a GCC compiler.</p>

<h4 class = "page-header">Install Homebrew</h2>
<p><strong>Instruction</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>To install run this command in terminal.</li>
  <pre>ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.github.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"</pre>
  <li>Verify installation was successful.</li>
  <pre>brew doctor</pre>
  <li>You should see:</li>
  <pre>Your system is ready to brew</pre>
</ol>
<p><strong>Reason</strong></p>
<p>Homebrew is a package management system that simplifies the installation of software.</p>

<h4 class = "page-header">Install iTerm2</h2>
<p><strong>Instruction</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li><a href = "http://iterm2.com/downloads.html">Download</a>.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Reason</strong></p>
